            <h2>4. Technology and Product Roadmap</h2>
            <p>Our platform evolves through continuous feature additions. AI-powered feature development, in particular, is the core of our business growth.</p>

            <h3>Development Phases</h3>
            <div class="service-detail">
              <h4>Phase 1 (Current) - Released</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Recruitment page creation and reward payment proxy features</li>
                <li>Participant search and application functions</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="service-detail">
              <h4>Phase 2 (Short-term) - In Development</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>Administrator dashboard</li>
                <li>Cancellation prevention features (evaluation system)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="service-detail">
              <h4>Phase 3 (Medium-term) - Planned</h4>
              <ul>
                <li>AI-powered recruitment effectiveness analysis engine</li>
                <li>Incentive features for repeat participants</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <h3>Strategic Partnership with Google Cloud</h3>
            <p>The above roadmap, especially the AI functionality and scalability that form the backbone of our business, are made possible by Google Cloud's advanced service portfolio.</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>AI Recruitment Analysis Engine:</strong> Leverage Vertex AI to build and deploy advanced predictive models</li>
              <li><strong>Data Infrastructure:</strong> Aggregate all platform data in BigQuery for real-time advanced analysis and AI model training</li>
              <li><strong>Scalable Infrastructure:</strong> Adopt Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE) to achieve high availability and auto-scaling</li>
              <li><strong>Core Services:</strong> Utilize Cloud SQL and Cloud Storage to build robust and stable service infrastructure</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

